
GIT WORKFLOW !!

Three Areas of GIT -> 

> Working Directory 
-- Where we make changes to our files. 
   Files here will be new, modified, or deleted. But, it won't save the changes until we stage and commit them.
> Staging Area 
-- Where we prepare changes before committing. 
> Repository 
-- Where our committed history is stored.
> Pushing Changes 
-- We can use this to send our commits to a remote repository like Github, so others can see them.
   [ git push ]
> Checking status 
-- To see which files are staged, unstaged or untracked. 
   [ git status ]

[working directory] -- git add --> [staging area] --git commit --> [Repository] 


> COMMANDS - 
-- Unstage a file and moving it out of staging area
   [ git restore --staged <file_name> ] 
-- Undo changes in working directory before staging 
   [ git restore <file> ] 
-- Undo our last commit, keeps changes in your working directory
   [ git reset HEAD~ ]
-- change the last commit message or add files to our last commit 
   [ git commit --amend ] 



